Run a Dataflow

Like recipes, you can run dataflows manually or schedule them to run automatically at regular intervals to create your datasets and keep the data up to date. You can also stop a dataflow while itâ€™s running.

You can schedule a dataflow to run after an event, such as when a sync job completes. Or you can schedule it to run hourly, weekly, monthly, or on specific days of the week or dates.

In Data Manager, the Monitor's Dataflows tab shows status, start time, and duration of the last 10 dataflow jobs. It retains the last 7 days of job history.

CRM Analytics uses version history to create copies of dataflows when you edit them so you can restore a previous version.

Set dataflow notifications to receive an email notification when a dataflow job finishes. You can be notified only when there are warnings, only when the dataflow fails, or every time the dataflow finishes.
